I felt like it.

1012
00:41:05,730 --> 00:41:06,798
You felt like what?

1013
00:41:08,466 --> 00:41:10,101
None of your business.

1014
00:41:10,101 --> 00:41:12,103
None of my business?

1015
00:41:12,103 --> 00:41:13,304
You just
destroyed my house!

1016
00:41:15,373 --> 00:41:16,507
So?

1017
00:41:16,507 --> 00:41:18,142
So?

1018
00:41:18,142 --> 00:41:20,011
So, you are
gonna get up,

1019
00:41:20,011 --> 00:41:21,446
and then you are gonna
go to school,

1020
00:41:21,446 --> 00:41:22,914
and you're gonna come
back here and clean it up,

1021
00:41:22,914 --> 00:41:24,148
and then you're gonna
pay for it!

1022
00:41:24,148 --> 00:41:25,316
You don't own me!

1023
00:41:25,316 --> 00:41:26,384
I'm your father!

1024
00:41:26,384 --> 00:41:27,452
You wish!

1025
00:41:27,452 --> 00:41:28,453
What's that
supposed to mean?

1026
00:41:28,453 --> 00:41:29,954
All you do
is you make rules

1027
00:41:29,954 --> 00:41:31,155
and you crack dumb jokes

1028
00:41:31,155 --> 00:41:33,324
and then you make promises
you're never gonna keep.

1029
00:41:33,324 --> 00:41:34,859
Hey, I got you
this house, didn't I?

1030
00:41:34,859 --> 00:41:35,927
I quit the gambling
business!

1031
00:41:35,927 --> 00:41:37,028
What do you
want from me?!

1032
00:41:37,028 --> 00:41:39,230
It didn't change you!

1033
00:41:39,230 --> 00:41:40,898
You're still the same!

1034
00:41:40,898 --> 00:41:43,034
You're just one big
phony big shot!

1035
00:41:43,034 --> 00:41:44,035
Ahh!

1036
00:41:44,035 --> 00:41:45,069
Ow!

1037
00:41:45,069 --> 00:41:46,804
♪♪

1038
00:41:46,804 --> 00:41:47,805
Get up.

1039
00:41:49,173 --> 00:41:50,208
Come on, get up
and go to school.

1040
00:41:52,477 --> 00:41:53,511
Amy, did you hear me?

1041
00:41:53,511 --> 00:41:55,179
You don't own me.

1042
00:41:55,179 --> 00:41:57,015
I have rights!

1043
00:41:57,015 --> 00:41:59,617
That's what
the social worker told me.

1044
00:41:59,617 --> 00:42:00,918
And you know what else
she told me?

1045
00:42:00,918 --> 00:42:04,088
She told me I don't have to
live here if I don't want to.

1046
00:42:04,088 --> 00:42:06,124
And I don't want to
live here.

1047
00:42:06,124 --> 00:42:07,725
(sobbing)

1048
00:42:11,863 --> 00:42:12,864
(sighing)

1049
00:42:16,467 --> 00:42:17,602
Look, I admit
I'm no Eisenstein

1050
00:42:17,602 --> 00:42:18,870
in the homework department,
all right?

1051
00:42:18,870 --> 00:42:22,140
But-- but every night
we eat ice cream together,

1052
00:42:22,140 --> 00:42:24,108
like a tradition.

1053
00:42:24,108 --> 00:42:26,611
I take her out in my boat,
I let her drive my car.

1054
00:42:26,611 --> 00:42:28,312
Ask her where she
learned to sing Fats Domino.

1055
00:42:28,312 --> 00:42:29,480
Go ahead, ask her.

1056
00:42:29,480 --> 00:42:30,948
(man)
And what about school?

1057
00:42:30,948 --> 00:42:32,950
There's nothing more
important than an education.

1058
00:42:32,950 --> 00:42:34,252
I sincerely believe that.

1059
00:42:34,252 --> 00:42:36,888
Exactly how do you support
her education, Mr. Ross?

1060
00:42:36,888 --> 00:42:38,322
I get her there,
rain or shine.

1061
00:42:38,322 --> 00:42:39,857
(woman)
That's it?

1062
00:42:39,857 --> 00:42:41,359
Well, what do I know
about those other things,

1063
00:42:41,359 --> 00:42:42,593
like history and so forth?

1064
00:42:42,593 --> 00:42:44,128
What do I know
about that?

1065
00:42:44,128 --> 00:42:46,431
Mr. Ross, you dropped out
of school when you were 15.

1066
00:42:46,431 --> 00:42:47,532
First criminal charge,

1067
00:42:47,532 --> 00:42:48,666
assault with
a deadly weapon--

1068
00:42:48,666 --> 00:42:50,034
(Johnny)
Hey, I was a kid,

1069
00:42:50,034 --> 00:42:53,438
I was drunk, I was waving
a broken beer bottle around.

1070
00:42:53,438 --> 00:42:54,539
What is that?

1071
00:42:54,539 --> 00:42:55,807
I object to this line
of questioning.

1072
00:42:55,807 --> 00:42:58,376
You ran numbers
in the garment district.

1073
00:42:58,376 --> 00:43:00,678
Did your father teach you
how to do that, Mr. Ross?

1074
00:43:00,678 --> 00:43:02,814
I don't
speak to my father.

1075
00:43:02,814 --> 00:43:05,817
I understand he was close
with Meyer Lansky in Miami.

1076
00:43:05,817 --> 00:43:06,818
(George)
That's enough.

1077
00:43:06,818 --> 00:43:08,052
You're badgering my cl--

1078
00:43:08,052 --> 00:43:10,988
Look, Meyer Lansky
would say hello to my father

1079
00:43:10,988 --> 00:43:13,191
when he was walking his dog
on Collins Avenue.

1080
00:43:13,191 --> 00:43:14,559
"Good morning, Mr. Lansky."

1081
00:43:14,559 --> 00:43:16,294
"Good morning,
Mr. Ross."

1082
00:43:16,294 --> 00:43:17,728
Now, is that a crime?

1083
00:43:17,728 --> 00:43:19,497
Does that make me
a lousy father?

1084
00:43:19,497 --> 00:43:20,998
Then you would like
to see your daughter

1085
00:43:20,998 --> 00:43:22,600
stay in school?

1086
00:43:22,600 --> 00:43:25,169
Well, of course I'd like to
see her continue in school.

1087
00:43:25,169 --> 00:43:28,105
Not only that, but after
she finishes high school,

1088
00:43:28,105 --> 00:43:29,540
I'm gonna foot the bill

1089
00:43:29,540 --> 00:43:31,843
so that she can go on to
blackjack dealer's school

1090
00:43:31,843 --> 00:43:33,878
in Vegas... if that's
what she wants.

1091
00:43:34,979 --> 00:43:36,147
I do not believe this.

1092
00:43:38,249 --> 00:43:39,917
So, they've
got plenty of room

1093
00:43:39,917 --> 00:43:41,786
and their daughter's
about your age.

1094
00:43:41,786 --> 00:43:44,388
So we thought the two
of you might hit it off.

1095
00:43:44,388 --> 00:43:45,756
Jim?

1096
00:43:45,756 --> 00:43:47,758
Whoa...
Hello, Amy.

1097
00:43:47,758 --> 00:43:49,727
What is this, you want me
to live with a cop?

1098
00:43:49,727 --> 00:43:52,263
Forget it.
Amy...

1099
00:43:52,263 --> 00:43:53,564
(man)
I said take your
hands off of me!

1100
00:43:53,564 --> 00:43:56,601
(men shouting)

1101
00:43:56,601 --> 00:43:57,902
I am on your
side, honey.

1102
00:43:59,370 --> 00:44:00,438
I like your father.

1103
00:44:00,438 --> 00:44:01,439
He's got
a good heart.

1104
00:44:01,439 --> 00:44:02,974
I know that.

1105
00:44:02,974 --> 00:44:05,243
Trouble is, he thinks
the shortest distance

1106
00:44:05,243 --> 00:44:07,512
between two points
is an angle.

1107
00:44:07,512 --> 00:44:09,280
I mean, he works
harder to steal a nickel

1108
00:44:09,280 --> 00:44:10,348
than it takes to
earn a dime.

1109
00:44:12,149 --> 00:44:14,018
Why are some
people like that?

1110
00:44:14,018 --> 00:44:15,019
Will they change?

1111
00:44:15,019 --> 00:44:16,287
I don't know.

1112
00:44:17,622 --> 00:44:18,823
I do know that
he loves you, though.

1113
00:44:20,358 --> 00:44:21,792
(sighing)

1114
00:44:21,792 --> 00:44:23,494
And I'll do
everything I can

1115
00:44:23,494 --> 00:44:25,029
to make sure that the two
of you get back together

1116
00:44:25,029 --> 00:44:26,163
in a better situation.

1117
00:44:28,065 --> 00:44:29,100
Sound fair?

1118
00:44:29,100 --> 00:44:30,301
(sighing)

1119
00:44:34,605 --> 00:44:37,875
(Jim)
Dear Father in heaven,
we thank you for this day.

1120
00:44:37,875 --> 00:44:42,146
God bless this wonderful
meal to our use...

1121
00:44:42,146 --> 00:44:43,748
and us to thy service.

1122
00:44:45,149 --> 00:44:47,118
And all God's
people said...

1123
00:44:47,118 --> 00:44:48,219
(all)
Amen.

1124
00:44:48,219 --> 00:44:49,587
Amen.

1125
00:44:49,587 --> 00:44:51,322
Amen.

1126
00:44:51,322 --> 00:44:52,557
All right, let's eat.

1127
00:44:52,557 --> 00:44:54,625
(knife whirring)

1128
00:44:58,129 --> 00:44:59,130
Movie star, huh?

1129
00:45:02,667 --> 00:45:05,169
♪♪

1130
00:45:28,793 --> 00:45:30,995
If I ever catch you with
any of my personal stuff,

1131
00:45:30,995 --> 00:45:32,430
you'll be out of here
so fast.

1132
00:45:35,333 --> 00:45:36,334
(Jim)
Bedtime, girls.

1133
00:45:36,334 --> 00:45:37,635
Knock off the chatter.

1134
00:45:37,635 --> 00:45:38,803
Good night, Dad.

1135
00:45:38,803 --> 00:45:39,870
Good night.

1136
00:45:41,639 --> 00:45:42,640
He thinks doing this

1137
00:45:42,640 --> 00:45:45,409
is some kind of huge
favor for mankind.

1138
00:45:45,409 --> 00:45:47,511
But your type
all end up the same.

1139
00:45:47,511 --> 00:45:50,147
Born a loser,
die a loser.

1140
00:45:50,147 --> 00:45:51,315
Trust me.

1141
00:46:10,034 --> 00:46:12,770
Beautiful color, scarlet,
don't you think?

1142
00:46:12,770 --> 00:46:14,238
Yeah.

1143
00:46:14,238 --> 00:46:15,406
Useful word, too.

1144
00:46:17,375 --> 00:46:20,711
"Scarlet Letter,"
"Scarlet Pimpernel,"

1145
00:46:20,711 --> 00:46:23,981
scarlet fever...
scarlet woman.

1146
00:46:26,283 --> 00:46:27,318
Hmm?

1147
00:46:27,318 --> 00:46:28,953
You wanted to see me.

1148
00:46:28,953 --> 00:46:31,455
Words are important,
Miss Ross.

1149
00:46:31,455 --> 00:46:32,657
They define
what you will be become.

1150
00:46:34,625 --> 00:46:37,528
You do want to become
something, don't you?

1151
00:46:37,528 --> 00:46:39,463
Yeah.

1152
00:46:39,463 --> 00:46:40,731
I don't know.

1153
00:46:50,174 --> 00:46:53,577
"Every atom belonging
to me as good...

1154
00:46:53,577 --> 00:46:54,578
belongs to you."

1155
00:47:03,087 --> 00:47:06,157
(laughing)

1156
00:47:07,158 --> 00:47:08,159
(girl)
Far out.

1157
00:47:16,801 --> 00:47:18,235
(girl)
I'd sort of like
a dad like that.

1158
00:47:18,235 --> 00:47:19,837
(girl)
I don't know.

1159
00:47:21,405 --> 00:47:22,406
(girl)
Look at the way he's dressed.

1160
00:47:22,406 --> 00:47:23,808
He's hilarious,
isn't he?

1161
00:47:23,808 --> 00:47:25,476
(girl)
Wow...

1162
00:47:28,679 --> 00:47:29,680
Get in.

1163
00:47:29,680 --> 00:47:30,881
Please,
get in the car.

1164
00:47:33,017 --> 00:47:35,820
(students laughing)

1165
00:47:38,689 --> 00:47:39,924
Go, go!

1166
00:47:39,924 --> 00:47:40,958
What's the problem
with you?

1167
00:47:40,958 --> 00:47:41,959
Just drive!

1168
00:47:41,959 --> 00:47:43,961
(engine revving)

1169
00:47:43,961 --> 00:47:45,563
(tires screeching)

1170
00:47:45,563 --> 00:47:46,864
I got permission,
if you want.

1171
00:47:46,864 --> 00:47:48,365
For what?

1172
00:47:48,365 --> 00:47:50,134
To be together,
just for the weekend.

1173
00:47:50,134 --> 00:47:52,136
You can help me
fix up my place.

1174
00:47:52,136 --> 00:47:53,637
What place?

1175
00:47:55,439 --> 00:47:56,540
I got a new business.

1176
00:47:56,540 --> 00:47:57,541
(scoffing)

1177
00:47:57,541 --> 00:47:58,876
Yeah, right.

1178
00:47:58,876 --> 00:48:00,177
It's legitimate.
Mm-hmm.

1179
00:48:00,177 --> 00:48:01,645
Tell me another one.

1180
00:48:01,645 --> 00:48:03,414
Hey...

1181
00:48:03,414 --> 00:48:04,415
I'm a man of my word.

1182
00:48:05,916 --> 00:48:06,917
Yeah.

1183
00:48:14,258 --> 00:48:16,093
♪♪

1184
00:48:16,093 --> 00:48:17,094
There it is.

1185
00:48:17,094 --> 00:48:18,229
What do you think?

1186
00:48:25,603 --> 00:48:27,738
Your dad made me
vice president.

1187
00:48:27,738 --> 00:48:29,340
That's great.

1188
00:48:29,340 --> 00:48:30,374
(bell dinging)

1189
00:48:31,976 --> 00:48:33,110
Hello.
Hi.

1190
00:48:33,110 --> 00:48:35,513
I'm here for the, uh,
demonstration.

1191
00:48:39,083 --> 00:48:40,785
(Johnny)
Now, ladies, this is one
of my favorite stitches.

1192
00:48:40,785 --> 00:48:42,453
You insert the cam here,

1193
00:48:42,453 --> 00:48:43,988
bring your material in
under the needle,

1194
00:48:43,988 --> 00:48:46,457
roll the needle
down in, drop the lock,

1195
00:48:46,457 --> 00:48:48,159
and we begin to sew.

1196
00:48:48,159 --> 00:48:50,261
It's as
simple as that.

1197
00:48:50,261 --> 00:48:53,864
And what we have is...
a beautiful stitch.

1198
00:48:53,864 --> 00:48:56,133
Oh, my...
Nice straight line.

1199
00:48:56,133 --> 00:48:58,202
Isn't that amazing?
(woman)
Oh, I can't believe it.

1200
00:48:58,202 --> 00:49:00,204
One of our
more perfect stitches.

1201
00:49:00,204 --> 00:49:02,907
It's a miracle.
Yes, it is.

1202
00:49:02,907 --> 00:49:05,376
Now, when you finish,
you bring the needle up,

1203
00:49:05,376 --> 00:49:07,111
drop the lock off here,

1204
00:49:07,111 --> 00:49:08,813
pull the material out,
take a snip,

1205
00:49:08,813 --> 00:49:11,448
and you have an
extraordinary stitch.

1206
00:49:11,448 --> 00:49:12,449
Now, this deluxe model

1207
00:49:12,449 --> 00:49:13,851
comes with
50 different cams

1208
00:49:13,851 --> 00:49:15,486
to vary the stitch
50 different times.

1209
00:49:17,421 --> 00:49:18,589
Any questions?
Yes, indeed.

1210
00:49:18,589 --> 00:49:19,590
Oh, I must have one--

1211
00:49:19,590 --> 00:49:21,025
Just for
the weekend.

1212
00:49:26,964 --> 00:49:28,232
(Johnny)
So, you got any homework?

1213
00:49:28,232 --> 00:49:30,167
It's Friday.

1214
00:49:30,167 --> 00:49:31,869
Well, you got tests,
stuff to write?

1215
00:49:31,869 --> 00:49:33,204
Dad, it's the weekend.

1216
00:49:33,204 --> 00:49:34,338
Hey, school comes first.

1217
00:49:34,338 --> 00:49:35,973
Oh, since when?

1218
00:49:35,973 --> 00:49:37,475
I'll help you.
(chuckling)

1219
00:49:37,475 --> 00:49:39,276
You don't know
anything about--
Don't know what?

1220
00:49:39,276 --> 00:49:40,711
Hey, go ahead,
ask me something.

1221
00:49:40,711 --> 00:49:42,279
And not just
two plus two, okay?

1222
00:49:42,279 --> 00:49:43,747
Ask me the hard stuff.

1223
00:49:43,747 --> 00:49:45,115
Hey, look,
check this out.

1224
00:49:45,115 --> 00:49:47,117
Three-way bulb.

1225
00:49:47,117 --> 00:49:48,619
Better for the eyes.
Dad.

1226
00:49:48,619 --> 00:49:50,621
Come on, you're old enough,
you're smart.

1227
00:49:50,621 --> 00:49:51,856
We should be talking
about important things,

1228
00:49:51,856 --> 00:49:52,857
like world events.

1229
00:49:52,857 --> 00:49:54,658
Come on,
ask me anything.

1230
00:49:54,658 --> 00:49:56,594
Geography, history,
science, go ahead.

1231
00:49:56,594 --> 00:49:57,928
Um, um...

1232
00:49:58,929 --> 00:50:00,164
Okay, okay, um...

1233
00:50:01,232 --> 00:50:03,234
How big...
is the moon?

1234
00:50:05,002 --> 00:50:06,003
The moon, huh?

1235
00:50:07,271 --> 00:50:08,973
(sighing)

1236
00:50:08,973 --> 00:50:10,441
That's a tough one.

1237
00:50:10,441 --> 00:50:11,876
The moon...

1238
00:50:11,876 --> 00:50:12,977
It's pretty big,
I know that.

1239
00:50:15,279 --> 00:50:17,414
I know, I know,
let's look it up.

1240
00:50:21,952 --> 00:50:23,287
Encyclopedia Britannica.

1241
00:50:23,287 --> 00:50:24,855
(laughing)

1242
00:50:24,855 --> 00:50:25,856
I read
the whole thing.

1243
00:50:25,856 --> 00:50:27,057
Very good books.

1244
00:50:27,057 --> 00:50:30,094
(blues playing)

1245
00:50:45,442 --> 00:50:46,443
You wanna
know how it works?
Yeah.

1246
00:50:46,443 --> 00:50:47,478
Okay.

1247
00:50:47,478 --> 00:50:49,647
The flywheel
turns the crankshaft.

1248
00:50:49,647 --> 00:50:51,215
Now, that makes
the pistons

1249
00:50:51,215 --> 00:50:53,217
go up and down
in the cylinders.

1250
00:50:53,217 --> 00:50:56,754
Then the timing chain
turns the camshaft

1251
00:50:56,754 --> 00:50:59,957
so that when it rotates,
the cams operate the valves.

1252
00:50:59,957 --> 00:51:01,225
Basic rock-'n'-roll.

1253
00:51:02,927 --> 00:51:04,161
(laughing)
Oh... Dad.

1254
00:51:09,466 --> 00:51:10,768
Is that beautiful
or is that beautiful?

1255
00:51:13,170 --> 00:51:14,672
That's beautiful.

1256
00:51:14,672 --> 00:51:16,040
(laughing)

1257
00:51:20,344 --> 00:51:23,747
(Amy)
"Long enough have you dreamed
contemptible dreams.

1258
00:51:23,747 --> 00:51:26,684
"Now I wash the gum
from your eyes.

1259
00:51:26,684 --> 00:51:28,819
"You must habit yourself
to the dazzle of the light

1260
00:51:28,819 --> 00:51:31,121
"and of every moment
of your life.

1261
00:51:31,121 --> 00:51:35,626
"Long have you timidly waded,
holding a plank by the shore.

1262
00:51:35,626 --> 00:51:39,129
"Now I will you
to be a bold swimmer,

1263
00:51:39,129 --> 00:51:41,565
"to jump off in the midst
of the sea,

1264
00:51:41,565 --> 00:51:45,202
"rise again,
nod to me, shout,

1265
00:51:45,202 --> 00:51:47,104
and laughingly dash
with your hair."

1266
00:52:10,527 --> 00:52:11,595
God, I don't
believe it.

1267
00:52:11,595 --> 00:52:12,663
Look what
he gave me.

1268
00:52:12,663 --> 00:52:14,198
