<i> in the Anchorage Bowl.</i>

1782
01:17:09,458 --> 01:17:11,594
<i> The area in the north</i>
<i> can expect</i>

1783
01:17:11,594 --> 01:17:12,962
<i> some flurries on Saturday.</i>

1784
01:17:12,962 --> 01:17:15,631
(foil crackling)

1785
01:17:18,067 --> 01:17:19,969
<i> And now Tom Tell</i>
<i> will bring us...</i>

1786
01:17:19,969 --> 01:17:21,003
(car horn honking)

1787
01:17:23,439 --> 01:17:25,541
(engine idling)

1788
01:17:32,915 --> 01:17:33,916
Hi.

1789
01:17:33,916 --> 01:17:35,718
So this is it, huh?

1790
01:17:35,718 --> 01:17:36,986
My plane
leaves in an hour.

1791
01:17:40,089 --> 01:17:41,357
I brought you
some catalogs.

1792
01:17:43,125 --> 01:17:44,960
They all have
scholarships.

1793
01:17:44,960 --> 01:17:46,228
What, are you dreaming?

1794
01:17:47,463 --> 01:17:49,131
Will you write to me?

1795
01:17:49,131 --> 01:17:50,533
Yeah, sure.

1796
01:17:52,401 --> 01:17:53,402
You too.

1797
01:17:58,641 --> 01:17:59,642
Take care of yourself.

1798
01:18:02,478 --> 01:18:03,579
(sniffling)

1799
01:18:05,648 --> 01:18:07,149
I'm gonna be okay.

1800
01:18:07,149 --> 01:18:08,317
I know that.

1801
01:18:14,256 --> 01:18:15,658
(engine revving)

1802
01:18:21,463 --> 01:18:22,598
(car horn honking)

1803
01:18:27,169 --> 01:18:28,170
(sniffling)

1804
01:18:29,738 --> 01:18:31,840
♪♪

1805
01:18:55,130 --> 01:18:56,165
(door creaking)

1806
01:18:57,433 --> 01:18:59,101
I can't wait here.

1807
01:18:59,101 --> 01:19:01,236
I know exactly
where he puts the boat.

1808
01:19:01,236 --> 01:19:02,237
I can help you,

1809
01:19:02,237 --> 01:19:04,173
just let me
come with you, please.

1810
01:19:04,173 --> 01:19:06,141
It's against
regulations, Amy.

1811
01:19:06,141 --> 01:19:07,142
(sighing)

1812
01:19:09,745 --> 01:19:10,813
This is Alaska.

1813
01:19:13,048 --> 01:19:14,116
Please.

1814
01:19:15,351 --> 01:19:16,752
(engine revving)

1815
01:19:22,591 --> 01:19:23,959
(Jim)
There's something I should
have told you before now.

1816
01:19:25,861 --> 01:19:27,196
You know the sewing machines
of your dad's?

1817
01:19:29,565 --> 01:19:31,267
He got them
on the gray market.

1818
01:19:31,267 --> 01:19:32,701
Meaning what?

1819
01:19:32,701 --> 01:19:34,036
They weren't hot.

1820
01:19:34,036 --> 01:19:35,037
He was legit.

1821
01:19:37,539 --> 01:19:38,540
Huh.

1822
01:19:40,276 --> 01:19:42,177
Man...

1823
01:19:42,177 --> 01:19:43,245
(chuckling)

1824
01:20:29,258 --> 01:20:30,759
(handle jiggling)

1825
01:20:42,237 --> 01:20:43,305
(grunting)

1826
01:20:45,808 --> 01:20:46,809
(sighing)

1827
01:20:48,043 --> 01:20:50,179
(Jim)
Hey, give me some backup
over at Eagle River.

1828
01:20:50,179 --> 01:20:52,081
I want a search warrant
for Cozart.

1829
01:20:52,081 --> 01:20:54,483
C-O-Z-A-R-T.

1830
01:20:56,151 --> 01:20:57,953
(man)
Bring him down to the car.

1831
01:20:57,953 --> 01:20:59,021
We got him.

1832
01:21:05,427 --> 01:21:06,795
Boo!
(man)
Get away from there!

1833
01:21:09,598 --> 01:21:11,834
Just need a couple more
minutes with these guys.

1834
01:21:11,834 --> 01:21:13,736
They resisted, so we have
to take 'em downtown.

1835
01:21:13,736 --> 01:21:14,770
(man)
You better come, sir.

1836
01:21:14,770 --> 01:21:15,771
We found him.

1837
01:21:16,772 --> 01:21:17,873
Amy!
No.

1838
01:21:17,873 --> 01:21:20,175
♪♪

1839
01:21:20,175 --> 01:21:21,210
(man)
Watch your step.

1840
01:21:21,210 --> 01:21:22,344
Uh, sir?

1841
01:21:27,349 --> 01:21:28,383
Come on,
it's all right.

1842
01:21:28,383 --> 01:21:29,384
Let's leave her
alone with him.

1843
01:21:32,054 --> 01:21:33,055
Oh...

1844
01:21:37,626 --> 01:21:39,161
(sobbing)

1845
01:21:52,341 --> 01:21:53,876
They told me about
the sewing machines.

1846
01:21:55,043 --> 01:21:57,479
I... didn't
believe you.

1847
01:21:58,647 --> 01:22:00,048
And I'm sorry.

1848
01:22:00,048 --> 01:22:02,251
(sobbing)

1849
01:22:05,521 --> 01:22:06,622
I don't even know

1850
01:22:06,622 --> 01:22:08,857
where you learned
to sew stitches like that.

1851
01:22:17,266 --> 01:22:19,434
(sobbing)

1852
01:22:19,434 --> 01:22:20,769
I'm still your girl.

1853
01:22:32,447 --> 01:22:33,515
(factory whistle blowing)

1854
01:22:36,885 --> 01:22:38,253
(drill whirring)

1855
01:22:48,463 --> 01:22:49,965
I'm not going today.

1856
01:22:49,965 --> 01:22:52,534
Is most sad day
in my life.

1857
01:22:55,537 --> 01:22:56,538
Thanks, T-Bone.

1858
01:23:02,778 --> 01:23:03,779
(door closing)

1859
01:23:05,247 --> 01:23:06,381
(woman)
You poor thing.

1860
01:23:06,381 --> 01:23:07,783
(woman)
Honey, you'll be okay.

1861
01:23:07,783 --> 01:23:09,318
(Angie sobbing)

1862
01:23:09,318 --> 01:23:10,452
(woman)
Here you go.

1863
01:23:10,452 --> 01:23:12,654
(woman)
This is so terrible.

1864
01:23:12,654 --> 01:23:14,590
Here, honey.

1865
01:23:14,590 --> 01:23:16,859
Go ahead.
Oh, God...

1866
01:23:16,859 --> 01:23:19,661
(car horn honking)

1867
01:23:23,198 --> 01:23:24,199
(tires screeching)

1868
01:23:26,835 --> 01:23:27,970
(woman)
I know it's awful.

1869
01:23:32,274 --> 01:23:33,575
(drill whirring)

1870
01:23:38,947 --> 01:23:39,948
Johnny's first rule.

1871
01:23:41,850 --> 01:23:42,851
Get the property back.

1872
01:23:48,090 --> 01:23:49,258
Thanks.

1873
01:23:49,258 --> 01:23:50,592
Uh, it'll take another
week for the boat.

1874
01:23:52,895 --> 01:23:54,096
Police found a letter

1875
01:23:54,096 --> 01:23:55,430
that they must have
tried to make him sign

1876
01:23:55,430 --> 01:23:57,099
to hand over Cindy's.

1877
01:23:57,099 --> 01:23:58,333
He must have
told them--

1878
01:23:58,333 --> 01:23:59,601
They were schmucks.

1879
01:24:01,904 --> 01:24:03,071
(chuckling)

1880
01:24:04,106 --> 01:24:05,741
♪♪

1881
01:25:17,746 --> 01:25:18,847
(sniffling)

1882
01:25:18,847 --> 01:25:20,215
(woman)
"Dear Mr. Ross.

1883
01:25:20,215 --> 01:25:21,683
"In response to your letter,

1884
01:25:21,683 --> 01:25:24,119
"I am delighted to inform you
that your daughter is achieving

1885
01:25:24,119 --> 01:25:26,822
"well above average grades
in all her subjects.

1886
01:25:26,822 --> 01:25:29,891
"I believe she has
an extremely bright future.

1887
01:25:29,891 --> 01:25:32,294
If you have any further
questions, please call me."

1888
01:25:50,045 --> 01:25:51,313
(car horn honking
in the distance)

1889
01:25:55,050 --> 01:25:56,318
(Angie)
Yeah, well, I'm his wife.

1890
01:25:56,318 --> 01:25:57,552
And I got rights.

1891
01:25:57,552 --> 01:25:59,121
That little kiddo
just better get used to it.

1892
01:26:16,071 --> 01:26:17,139
(engine revving)

1893
01:26:23,145 --> 01:26:24,746
Amy, Amy, wait, wait.

1894
01:26:24,746 --> 01:26:25,747
Open up.

1895
01:26:27,716 --> 01:26:29,451
I'm sorry,
I'm really sorry.

1896
01:26:29,451 --> 01:26:30,519
I gotta go.

1897
01:26:32,320 --> 01:26:34,122
Your daddy loved you, Amy.

1898
01:26:34,122 --> 01:26:35,824
He thought about
you all the time.

1899
01:26:35,824 --> 01:26:37,459
I mean all the time,
and you know that.

1900
01:26:37,459 --> 01:26:38,627
(sniffling)

1901
01:26:41,696 --> 01:26:42,697
I'll see ya.

1902
01:26:46,868 --> 01:26:48,303
Hey!

1903
01:26:48,303 --> 01:26:50,205
Where do you think
you're going?

1904
01:26:50,205 --> 01:26:52,374
That is my Cadillac!

1905
01:26:52,374 --> 01:26:53,675
I own that now!

1906
01:26:54,709 --> 01:26:56,745
Come back here,
you little moron!

1907
01:26:56,745 --> 01:26:58,980
♪♪

1908
01:27:08,423 --> 01:27:10,826
(sobbing quietly)

1909
01:27:30,345 --> 01:27:35,784
(tires screeching)

1910
01:27:47,062 --> 01:27:49,164
(sobbing)

1911
01:27:53,535 --> 01:27:54,536
(bird squawking)

1912
01:27:54,536 --> 01:27:55,904
♪♪

1913
01:27:55,904 --> 01:27:57,672
(bird squawking)

1914
01:28:04,312 --> 01:28:06,114
(bird squawking)

1915
01:28:14,456 --> 01:28:17,159
(bird squawking)

1916
01:28:20,929 --> 01:28:21,930
(thundering)

1917
01:28:21,930 --> 01:28:23,165
(bird squawking)

1918
01:28:27,235 --> 01:28:29,337
(crying)

1919
01:28:34,109 --> 01:28:35,277
(bird squawking)

1920
01:28:49,457 --> 01:28:51,193
(bird squawking)

1921
01:28:53,295 --> 01:28:54,796
(sighing)

1922
01:28:56,865 --> 01:28:58,533
(bird squawking)

1923
01:29:00,902 --> 01:29:04,306
♪♪

1924
01:29:07,342 --> 01:29:08,343
(tires screeching)

1925
01:29:12,647 --> 01:29:13,715
Get out of here.

1926
01:29:52,988 --> 01:29:53,989
(door closing)

1927
01:30:08,303 --> 01:30:09,571
What did you
think of his poems?

1928
01:30:12,207 --> 01:30:13,208
They don't rhyme.

1929
01:30:18,813 --> 01:30:20,482
(school bell ringing)

1930
01:30:22,217 --> 01:30:25,387
(students chattering)

1931
01:30:39,367 --> 01:30:41,269
♪♪
